    <center><table class="itemDisplayTable">
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Title:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Conceptual Defense Structure Employing Cloud Computing In Military Applications</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Authors:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Magesh.S</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Keywords:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Conceptual Defense Structure<br />Cloud Computing</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Issue Date:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Jul-2013 </td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Publisher:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">SRM University</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Series/Report no.:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">T0138</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Abstract:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Countries across the world are continuously striving to improve their
strength against any invasion through the sophistication of their defense. In this
aspect, efforts are being taken to integrate various technology developments with
military applications. Keeping the above in mind, this dissertation focuses on
evolving a new defense structure with cutting edge technologies. The proposed
defense structure aims at plugging Wireless Sensor Networks (WSNs) deployed for
variety of operations in military with cloud computing. Cloud computing is used in
the military scenario as private defense cloud in my dissertation. This cloud
encompasses various functional centers of military within its perimeter and the
scope of defense cloud is extended to reach the WSNs present in the battlefield
through the cloud gateway. Hence, cloud gateway is considered to be the heart of
structure. The novelty of this structure lies in the integration of military WSNs with
private defense cloud through the cloud gateway. For this, a careful study on the
feasibility of porting cloud technology into military and integrating the same with
military WSN is performed.
WSNâ€™s efficiency is critical to the success of any military network.
Often, the operation of WSN is affected by the notion of time possessed by nodes.
Uniformity with respect to time among nodes shall be provided by time
synchronization. In the context of the proposed defense structure, I have proposed a
new time synchronization scheme based on relative drift of clock among nodes. The
time synchronization scheme proposed in this dissertation showed improved performance in reducing the relative drift under conditions of huge number of nodes
and clusters, as is present in the military WSNs. The results obtained through
simulations evidently prove the same in comparison with widely used time
synchronization scheme, Timing Sync Protocol for Sensor Networks (TPSN). In
addition to reducing the relative drift among nodes, our scheme conserves the energy
consumption in nodes by reducing the number of transmissions required for time
synchronization. The clustering process in the military WSNs is carried out based on
LEACH algorithm and simulations are performed using MATLAB.
Flow of information across different entities in military is critical to
many important decisions to be taken. In this aspect, transmission of data packets
and flow of information from military sensor networks to the appropriate operational
centers of defense should be carried out with utmost care. For this data transmission,
in the presence of private defense cloud via cloud gateway, an operation research
technique is employed in the form of queuing theory for servicing the packets at the
cloud gateway. At the cloud gateway M/G/1 queuing model is employed. We have
utilized pre emptive priority service discipline to calculate the average waiting time
and service time of high priority and normal packets. These parameters are taken
into account as part of Quality of Service analysis. The results obtained through
simulation using Java Modeling tools prove that the average waiting time and
service time obtained, align well with the theoretical analysis.
Maintaining security has always been the need for military
communication. From the perspective of proposed defense structure, we have
employed a modified Kerberos protocol to perform node level authentication at the cloud gateway for cluster heads and user level authentication at the cloud gateway
for different military personnel present in various operational centers. CloudAnalyst,
Heimdal distribution of Kerberos, and Advanced Encryption Scheme (AES) are
used to compute the response times for node level and user level authentication
using single realm and cross realm configurations. The response times obtained with
the modified Kerberos are less compared to the normal Kerberos in all cases.
Hence, this dissertation in a nutshell presents a conceptual defense
structure employing WSNs and cloud technology. It also provides techniques and
methods to deal with time synchronization, data transmission, and efficient and
secure authentication.</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">URI:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue"><a href="http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/15147">http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/15147</a></td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Appears in Collections:</td><td class="metadataFieldValue"><a href="/dspace/handle/123456789/6855">Ph.D - Thesis  </a><br/></td></tr>
